## Game Master Guidance

### Shields in Combat

Remember that shields occupy one hand:
- Can't use two-handed weapons (except bucklers)
- Can't wield versatile weapons two-handed
- Can't dual-wield or use off-hand items
- Can use medium or light weapons one-handed

The trade-off is intentional—shields provide substantial defensive benefit at meaningful offensive cost.

### Shield Upgrades

Shields can be enhanced like other equipment:
- **Masterwork:** Improved construction, lighter weight (reduce weight class by one)
- **Magical +1/+2/+3:** Additional Guard bonus beyond base value
- **Special Properties:** Spell reflection, extra DR, resistance to specific damage types

When rewarding magical shields, remember they're highly valuable for defensive builds. A +1 medium shield (total +3 Guard) significantly improves survivability.

### Balancing Shield Users

Characters with shields are harder to hit but deal standard damage. Adjust encounters by:
- Adding more enemies (shields don't help against being outnumbered)
- Using effects that bypass Guard (forced movement, conditions, environmental hazards)
- Targeting unshielded allies (make shield users choose between protecting themselves and others)

Don't punish players for using shields—let them feel effective at the defensive role they chose.

